es. We don't have uber gear though.  No, i don't play a mage (though i do have a 51 necro).  I do know a 59 mage that has been absolutely tearing through levels though because he's finding soloing/duoing for experience both easy and fast, much faster than bothering with a larger group even when the group is almost all L60's.  I have heard of other classes who solo or duo that are also outpacing larger group experience by a fair margin and that that's something verant says they are &quot;looking at&quot;.  They may increase the epxerience for higher level mobs that pretty much require groups to kill.  The faster exp is just a very pronounced difference with a mage.  He does not have much downtime at all and if he gets KEI then it's virtually zero downtime.  In a larger exp group, where if he's there we'll almost always pull 2 or more mobs at a time, he's very clearly the dominate damage dealer even when a 60 epic rogue is present.  Damagewise in our exp groups, nothing is coming close to the epic water pet tanking a mob with mage nukes thrown in too, not even the rogue.  It's an amazing class to have in your group if you want experience.  Given the incredible damage the class can already pump out, I couldn't believe this player question and verant employee answer posted on caster's realm today -- <br>
<br>
&quot;Will they ever remove the pet haste cap?<br>
<br>
Yes, this is something that’s been recently discussed. We’ll most likely be changing it in a way that will be viewed as a universal positive. Unless you’re being attacked by a pet. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> &quot;<br>
<br>
/boggle.  another pet upgrade?  Sorry, for me this confirms what I was already thinking.  Verant either has no clue whatsoever how to balance classes or they just don't care.  They watch their percentages and if a class isn't played enough, upgrade time! wheeee!  I really believe that's how Verant makes many (not all! i know there's always exceptions <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) of their balance changes.  It's classic MUD operator mentality.  Pump up the underplayed classes.  The tone of the panel responses on the Q&amp;A from caster's realm suggests even more caster upgrades coming soon.<br>
